        <updateDate>2021-06-29T19:09:01Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Fair Returns for Public Lands Act of 2021</b></p> <p>This bill revises the royalty system applicable to leases of public lands for oil and gas production. </p> <p>Specifically, it increases royalty rates, rental rates, and minimum bidding standards for onshore oil and gas leasing. In addition, it establishes a new fee that must be paid by any person who nominates public lands for such leasing.</p> <p>Finally, the bill requires the Department of the Interior to adjust these rates and fees for inflation at least every four years.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
